label: obsolete_addition of molecular label
example of usage: The addition of phycoerytherin label to an anti-CD8 antibody, to label all antibodies. The addition of anti-CD8-PE to a population of cells, to label the subpopulation cells that are CD8+.

label: obsolete_fine needle biopsy
definition: A biopsy that uses a thin, hollow needle to draw cells from a body.
term editor: Person: Chris Stoeckert, Helena Ellis, Jie Zheng

label: obsolete_core needle biopsy
definition: A biopsy that uses a hollow tube that allows extracting a core of tissue for testing. This type of needle biopsy uses a wider needle than does fine-needle aspiration.
term editor: Person: Chris Stoeckert, Helena Ellis, Jie Zheng
